Option.Name: Straight Sword / Greatsword / Ultra Greatsword / Whip
One hand down and behind hip

behaviorVariationId.Wiki: Behavior Variation ID determines the damage multipliers used during specific moves (known as 'motion values'), Speffects to apply to the target or the player and which bullets to spawn.

sortId.Wiki: This controls the position of the weapon in your menu. Note that reinforcement will add the current level of reinforcement to this ID, so you need to space the ID properly between infusion entries.

weight.Wiki: The Weight value showed in the game menu

fixPrice.Wiki: This is the amount of souls Andre will take to fix this item

basicPrice.Wiki: The base soul cost it will take to reinforce this item, scales with each consecutive upgrade.

sellValue.Wiki: The souls given when this item is sold.

correctStrength.Wiki: The base scaling value used for Strenght. Note that this is multiplied by reinforcement (via ReinforceParamWeapon).

correctAgility.Wiki: The base scaling value used for Dexterity. Note that this is multiplied by reinforcement (via ReinforceParamWeapon).

corretMagic.Wiki: The base scaling value used for Intelligence. Note that this is multiplied by reinforcement (via ReinforceParamWeapon).

corretFaith.Wiki: The base scaling value used for Faith. Note that this is multiplied by reinforcement (via ReinforceParamWeapon).

physGuardCutRate.Wiki: The Physical absorption to use when guarding.

magGuardCutRate.Wiki: The Magic absorption to use when guarding.

fireGuardCutRate.Wiki: The Fire absorption to use when guarding.

thunGuardCutRate.Wiki: The Lightning absorption to use when guarding.

spEffectBehaviorId0.Wiki: The SpEffect to apply to the enemy on hit. Typically used for Poison, Bleed, etc.

spEffectBehaviorId1.Wiki: The SpEffect to apply to the enemy on hit. Typically used for Poison, Bleed, etc.

spEffectBehaviorId2.Wiki: The SpEffect to apply to the enemy on hit. Typically used for Poison, Bleed, etc.

residentSpEffectId0.Wiki: The SpEffect to apply passively to the player while holding the item in the active hand.

residentSpEffectId1.Wiki: The SpEffect to apply passively to the player while holding the item in the active hand.

residentSpEffectId2.Wiki: The SpEffect to apply passively to the player while holding the item in the active hand.

materialSetId.Wiki: Determines the EquipMtrlSetParam row range used for reinforcement.

antUndeadDamageRate.Wiki: Modifies damage against Undead-type enemies (i.e. Skeletons).

equipModelId.Wiki: The part model ID. Determines the part model used by the weapon.

iconId.Wiki: The icon index ID. Determines the icon used by the weapon.

durability.Wiki: This value determines how quickly your durability is drained by attacks, lower equals faster, higher equals slower

durailityMax.Wiki: This the maximum durability, it will be shown in the game GUI

atkBasePhysics.Wiki: The base Physical damage. Note that this is multiplied by reinforcement (via ReinforceParamWeapon).

atkBaseMagic.Wiki: The base Magic damage. Note that this is multiplied by reinforcement (via ReinforceParamWeapon).

atkBaseFire.Wiki: The base Fire damage. Note that this is multiplied by reinforcement (via ReinforceParamWeapon).

atkBaseThunder.Wiki: The base Lightning damage. Note that this is multiplied by reinforcement (via ReinforceParamWeapon).

atkBaseStamina.Wiki: The base Stamina damage that is applied to an enemy when guarding. Note that this is multiplied by reinforcement (via ReinforceParamWeapon).

saWeaponDamage.Wiki: The base Poise damage. Note that this is multiplied by reinforcement (via ReinforceParamWeapon).

saDurability.Wiki: This most likely does nothing, but it is named just in case.

staminaGuardDef.Wiki: This is the (Stability) value in the game menu. It determines how much stamina is consumed while blocking with this item, higher stability means less stamina is consumed.

reinforceTypeId.Wiki: ID of ReinforceParamWeapon to use for calculating the effects of reinforcement.

throwAtkRate.Wiki: The critical multiplier applied when Riposting or Backstabbing an enemy.

bowDistRate.Wiki: The bow distance added to ammunition range.

wepmotionCategory.Wiki: Determines the base moveset used by the weapon. Corresponds to TAE ID.

guardmotionCategory.Wiki: Determines the moveset used whilst guarding.

correctType.Wiki: ID of CalcCorrectGraph to use for calculating how stats affect scaling.

spAtkCategory.Wiki: Determines the override moveset used by the weapon. Corresponds to TAE ID.

properStrength.Wiki: Determines the level of Strenght required to wield this weapon.

properAgility.Wiki: Determines the level of Dexterity required to wield this weapon

properMagic.Wiki: Determines the level of Intelligence required to wield this weapon.

properFaith.Wiki: Determines the level of Faith required to wield this weapon.

poisonGuardResist.Wiki: The Poison resistance this item will have while guarding

toxicGuardResist.Wiki: The Toxic resistance this item will have while guarding

bloodGuardResist.Wiki: The Bleed resistance this item will have while guarding

curseGuardResist.Wiki: The Curse resistance this item will have while guarding. This will not affect the Basilisk's curse mist.

rightHandEquipable.Wiki: This value determines wheter this item can be equipped in right hand slots.

leftHandEquipable.Wiki: This value determines wheter this item can be equipped in left hand slots.

bothHandEquipable.Wiki: This value determines wheter this item can be 2 handed.

arrowSlotEquipable.Wiki: Determines wheter this item can be equipped in the arrow slots.

boltSlotEquipable.Wiki: Determines wheter this item can be equipped in the bolt slots.

enableGuard.Wiki: Determines whether this weapon can guard (requires TAE support for actual effect).

enableParry.Wiki: Determines whether this weapon can parry (requires TAE support for actual effect).

enableMagic.Wiki: Determines whether this weapon can cast Sorceries (requires HKS or TAE support for actual effect).

enablePyromancy.Wiki: Determines whether this weapon can cast Pyromancies (requires HKS or TAE support for actual effect).

enableMiracle.Wiki: Determines whether this weapon can cast Miracles (requires HKS or TAE support for actual effect).

enableVowMagic.Wiki: Determines whether this weapon can cast Covenant spells.\n(For your information. None are present in ds3, but it can be used as a fourth magic school.)\n(requires HKS or TAE support for actual effect.)

isNormalAttackType.Wiki: Display Standard as the damage type in the weapon menu. Actual type is defined in BehaviorParam_PC.

isBlowAttackType.Wiki: Display Strike as the damage type in the weapon menu. Actual type is defined in BehaviorParam_PC.

isSlashAttackType.Wiki: Display Slash as the damage type in the weapon menu. Actual type is defined in BehaviorParam_PC.

isThrustAttackType.Wiki: Display Thrust as the damage type in the weapon menu. Actual type is defined in BehaviorParam_PC.

isEnhance.Wiki: Determines whether this weapon can be buffed via SpEffects.

isLuckCorrect.Wiki: Likely has to do with luck scaling, but it's function is unknown to this day.

isCustom.Wiki: Determines whether this weapon can be reinforced.

isDarkHand.Wiki: Pretty self explanatory, it is only used for Dark Hand in vanilla.

wepAbsorpPosId.Wiki: This determines what Sheat Position ID to use, this value is found in WepAbsorpPosParam

Unk12.Wiki: Determines the multiplier to apply to Toughness (when applied via InvokeToughness in TAE).

Unk14.Wiki: This determines wheter the item is a paired weapon.\nActual effects include. enabling the L1 moveset when 2 handing and changing the animation that plays when 2 handing.\nThe hand change animation can be fixed in HKS if your weapon isn't a twinblade but you still want the L1 moveset.

IsAutoEquip.Wiki: Automatically equips the item when picked up, it is normally only used in bolts/arrows.

Unk21.Wiki: Determines the stat graph used for Magic damage (i.e. how effective a stat is).

Unk22.Wiki: Determines the stat graph used for Fire damage (i.e. how effective a stat is).

Unk23.Wiki: Determines the stat graph used for Lightning damage (i.e. how effective a stat is).

darkGuardCutRate.Wiki: The Dark absorption to use when guarding.

atkBaseDark.Wiki: The base Dark damage. Note that this is multiplied by reinforcement (via ReinforceParamWeapon).

Unk26.Wiki: Determines the stat graph used for Dark damage (i.e. how effective a stat is).

Unk31.Wiki: The Frost resistance to use when guarding.

swordArtId.Wiki: Determines the SwordArtsParam ID to use.

correctLuck.Wiki: The base scaling value used for Luck. Note that this is multiplied by reinforcement (via ReinforceParamWeapon).

weaponVfx0.Wiki: Vfx ID to apply to your item

weaponVfx1.Wiki: Vfx ID to apply to your item

weaponVfx2.Wiki: Vfx ID to apply to your item

weaponVfx3.Wiki: Vfx ID to apply to your item

weaponVfx4.Wiki: Dummy ID at which to position your Vfx ID 1

weaponVfx5.Wiki: Dummy ID at which to position your Vfx ID 2

weaponVfx6.Wiki: Dummy ID at which to position your Vfx ID 3

weaponVfx7.Wiki: Dummy ID at which to position your Vfx ID 4

StaminaConsumeRate.Wiki: The stamina multiplier applied to the stamina costs defined in behavior.

shopPrice.Wiki: The soul cost of the weapon in a shop.
